  "exec_summary": "The European Banking Authority has launched a consultation on the first four mandates under the DGSD3, which aims to enhance regulatory standards for banks. In Belgium, the Financial Services and Markets Authority and the National Bank of Belgium continue to oversee the implementation of EU regulations, including the recently published Commission Delegated Regulation on firms' order execution policies under MiFID II. The European Commission's delegated regulation provides clarity on the requirements for firms to establish and implement order execution policies. Meanwhile, Deutsche Bank is under scrutiny, with its headquarters raided for the third time this year amid a tax fraud probe, highlighting the importance of regulatory compliance and anti-money laundering efforts.",
